  "texts": [
    "Over time, IL has required specific expansion related to grade-level and subject matter, and to keep pace with the evolution of new technologies (e.g., computer, digital, internet, media, news) [31,32].",
    "Information literacy takes on added importance in the setting of global health due to differences among international states.",
    "To emphasize the importance of an information literate society on the global level, the United Nations Educational, Scientific and Cultural Organization (UNESCO) partnered with the International Federation of Library Associations and Institutions (IFLA) to convene \"expert meetings\" that culminated in the Prague Declaration (2003) [33] and the Alexandria Proclamation (2005) [34].",
    "These documents emphasize that IL is a basic human right \"assisting individuals and their institutions to meet technological, economic and social challenges, to redress disadvantage and to advance the well-being of all [34]. \"",
    "Given these priorities, the latest advances in information technology giving rise to GenAI tools must also be evaluate in the context of IL."
  ],
